27/06/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- The country's National Security Council (MGK) decided on Thursday (June 26th) to continue the fight against terrorism and the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) resolutely. 
At a regular meeting chaired by President Abdullah Gul, the MGK discussed problems the country faces in its anti-terrorism efforts, as well as energy issues and the situation in Iraq. 
According to a statement issued after the meeting, council members agreed Turkey should take maximum advantage of renewable energy sources amid high energy demand. 
They also vowed to boost co-operation with neighbouring countries and Turkey's role as an energy transit country. 
(Hurriyet - 27/06/08; Anadolu news agency - 26/06/08)
